Subject: [Bioc-devel] New Bioconductor package: intansv
Message-ID: <!&!AAAAAAAAAAAYAAAAAAAAALOUEX7GvYpEtmp+J90rZZ7CgAAAEAAAAHEtBm1my75GiAHZtMXHZKIBAAAAAA==@gmail.com>

Dear Bioconductor Users,

I would like to announce the release of our new package intansv.

Currently, dozens of softwares have been developed to predict structural
variations (SV) utilizing next generation sequencing data. However, the
prediction of multiple methods have to be integrated to get relatively
reliable results. The intansv package is designed for integrating results of
different methods, annotating effects caused by SVs to genes and its
elements, displaying the genomic distribution of SVs and visualizing SVs in
specific genomic region.

